== Related Articles == * [[:en:Laba Festival|Laba Festival]] {{Month (Calendar)|Lunisolar December|List of Lunisolar Dates|Month (Lunisolar)|12|Day (Lunisolar)|{{ill|December 30 (Lunisolar)|ja|12月30日 (旧暦)|lt=30|lt_ja=30|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/December 30 (Lunisolar)|qq=}}|qq=}}
{{Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} {{short description|Month of the Chinese calendar|qq=}} {{more citations needed |date=June 2024|qq=}} {{italic title|qq=}}
'''''Làyuè''''' ({{zh|s=腊月|qq=}}) is the last month of the year in the [[:en:Chinese calendar|Chinese calendar]]. In general, the [[:en:Dahan (solar term)|Great Cold]], the 24th [[solar term]], is in ''Làyuè''. The name comes from the winter sacrifice, just as February. In Japan, the month known as {{nihongo|Shiwasu|師走||{{lit|priests' busiest month|qq=}}|qq=}}.
==Festival== *The [[:en:Laba Festival|Laba Festival]] is ''Layue'' 8.<ref name="chinadaily">{{Cite web |last=CGTN |date=January 12, 2024 |title=Layue, a joyful celebration in the run-up to Spring Festival |url=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/202401/12/WS65a09b0da3105f21a507bf3a.html |access-date=12 June 2024 |website=China Daily|qq=}}</ref> The original definition of the Laba festival was the day of the winter sacrifice ({{zh|t=臘日|s=腊日|qq=}}), and the date is the third ''Wùrì'' after the Winter Solstice. *The Preliminary Eve ({{zh|s=小年|qq=}}) is ''Layue'' 23. *The New Year's Eve ({{zh|s=除夕|qq=}}) is the last day of the year, ''Layue'' 29 or 30.
==Events== [[:en:Aisin-Gioro Puyi|Aisin-Gioro Puyi]], the 12th [[:en:Qing dynasty|Qing]] emperor of [[:en:China|China]], issued the imperial abdication edict on ''Layue'' 25, 1911.
==Births== *[[:en:Emperor Go-Uda|Emperor Go-Uda]], the 91st [[:en:Emperor of Japan|emperor]] of [[:en:Japan|Japan]], ''Shiwasu'' 1, 1269 *[[Tokugawa Ieyasu]], the founder and first ''[[shōgun]]'' of the [[Tokugawa shogunate]] of Japan, ''Shiwasu'' 26, 1542 *[[:en:Uemura Masahisa|Uemura Masahisa]], a Japanese Christian pastor, theologian and critic of Meiji and Taishō periods, ''Shiwasu'' 1, 1857 *[[:en:Imperial Noble Consort Shushen|Imperial Noble Consort Shushen]], an Imperial concubine of the [[Tongzhi Emperor]], ''Làyuè'' 1, 1859
==Deaths== *[[Yue Fei]], Yue Yun, Zhang Xian, military generals who lived in the [[Southern Song dynasty]], ''Làyuè 29<sub>th</sub> 1141'' *[[:en:Lu You|Lu You]], a prominent poet of China's Southern Song dynasty, ''Làyuè 29<sub>th</sub> 1209'' *[[:en:Emperor Go-Hanazono|Emperor Go-Hanazono]], the 102nd emperor of Japan, ''Shiwasu 27<sub>th</sub> 1470'' *[[:en:Lê Uy Mục|Lê Uy Mục]], the eighth king of the later [[:en:Lê dynasty|Lê dynasty]] of Vietnam, ''Làyuè 1<sub>st</sub> 1509'' *[[Yi Gwang-sik]], a Korean politician and general during the [[:en:Joseon dynasty|Joseon dynasty]], ''Làyuè 1<sub>st</sub> 1563''
